{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🛰️ GeoAI Land Classification - Exploratory Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the complete workflow for satellite imagery analysis and land cover classification.\n",
    "\n",
    "**All tools used are FREE:**\n",
    "- Python (open-source)\n",
    "- Jupyter Notebook (open-source)\n",
    "- Scikit-learn (open-source)\n",
    "- Matplotlib/Plotly (open-source)\n",
    "- Sentinel-2 data (free from ESA)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup and Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import plotly.express as px\n",
    "import plotly.graph_objects as go\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, classification_report\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append('../src')\n",
    "\n",
    "from data_loader import SatelliteDataLoader\n",
    "from model import LandCoverClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "print('✅ All libraries imported successfully!')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Load Satellite Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize data loader\n",
    "loader = SatelliteDataLoader(data_dir='../data/raw')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load sample data for Amazon region\n",
    "data = loader.load_sample_data(region='amazon')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"RGB image shape: {data['rgb'].shape}")\n",
    "print(f"NIR band shape: {data['nir'].shape}")\n",
    "print(f"Metadata: {data['metadata']}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Visualize Satellite Bands"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].imshow(data['rgb'])\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('RGB Composite')\n",
    "axes[0].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[1].imshow(data['nir'], cmap='gray')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('NIR Band')\n",
    "axes[1].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[2].imshow(data['swir'], cmap='gray')\n",
    "axes[2].set_title('SWIR Band')\n",
    "axes[2].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Calculate Vegetation Index (NDVI)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate NDVI\n",
    "ndvi = loader.calculate_ndvi(data['rgb'][:,:,0], data['nir'])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "plt.imshow(ndvi, cmap='RdYlGn', vmin=-1, vmax=1)\n",
    "plt.colorbar(label='NDVI')\n",
    "plt.title('Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI)')\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"NDVI Statistics:\n  Mean: {ndvi.mean():.3f}\n  Min: {ndvi.min():.3f}\n  Max: {ndvi.max():.3f}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Train Land Cover Classifier"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize classifier\n",
    "classifier = LandCoverClassifier(n_estimators=100, max_depth=20)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train model\n",
    "metrics = classifier.train(data['rgb'], data['nir'], data['swir'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print("\nClassification Report:")\n",
    "print(metrics['classification_report'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Feature Importance Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "importance = classifier.get_feature_importance()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = px.bar(\n",
    "    x=list(importance.keys()),\n",
    "    y=list(importance.values()),\n",
    "    labels={'x': 'Feature', 'y': 'Importance'},\n",
    "    title='Feature Importance in Land Cover Classification',\n",
    "    color=list(importance.values()),\n",
    "    color_continuous_scale='viridis'\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Make Predictions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Predict on the same image (for demonstration)\n",
    "predictions, probabilities = classifier.predict(data['rgb'], data['nir'], data['swir'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize predictions\n",
    "class_names = ['Water', 'Forest', 'Agriculture', 'Urban', 'Barren', 'Grassland', 'Wetland']\n",
    "colors = ['#1f77b4', '#2ca02c', '#ff7f0e', '#d62728', '#8c564b', '#9467bd', '#17becf']\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "plt.imshow(data['rgb'])\n",
    "plt.title('Original RGB')\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
    "plt.imshow(predictions, cmap='tab10')\n",
    "plt.title('Land Cover Classification')\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create custom legend\n",
    "from matplotlib.patches import Patch\n",
    "legend_elements = [Patch(facecolor=colors[i], label=class_names[i]) for i in range(7)]\n",
    "plt.legend(handles=legend_elements, bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Confusion Matrix"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cm = metrics['confusion_matrix']\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = px.imshow(\n",
    "    cm,\n",
    "    labels=dict(x="Predicted", y="Actual", color="Count"),\n",
    "    x=class_names,\n",
    "    y=class_names,\n",
    "    title='Confusion Matrix',\n",
    "    color_continuous_scale='Blues'\n",
    ")\n",
    "fig.update_traces(text=cm, texttemplate='%{text}')\n",
    "fig.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Save Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "classifier.save_model('../models/random_forest_model.pkl')\n",
    "print("✅ Model saved successfully!")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrated:\n",
    "1. ✅ Loading satellite imagery data\n",
    "2. ✅ Visualizing multispectral bands\n",
    "3. ✅ Calculating spectral indices (NDVI)\n",
    "4. ✅ Training a Random Forest classifier\n",
    "5. ✅ Evaluating model performance\n",
    "6. ✅ Making predictions on new data\n",
    "7. ✅ Saving the trained model\n",
    "\n",
    "**All using 100% FREE tools and data!**"
   ]
  }
